<tr><td valign="top"><font face='Arial,Sans-Serif' size='-1'><div align="justify">

<table border=0 width=100%>
   <tr>
      <td align=center valign=top width=88px><a href="life/pics.aspx?id=portrait"><img alt=""
         border=0 hspace=0 src="life/pics/portrait.gif"></a><br /><font face=Arial size=1>H.P.
         Lovecraft<br />(1890&ndash;1937)<br /></font></td>
      <td rowspan=2>&nbsp;<br /></td>
      <td rowspan=2 valign=top><b>H<font size=-1>OWARD</font> P<font size=-1>HILLIPS</font> L<font
         size=-1>OVECRAFT</font></b> (20 August 1890&ndash;15 March 1937) is probably best known as
         a writer of weird fiction, but some believe his voluminous correspondence to be his
         greatest accomplishment. You can explore his numerous facets through the many pages
         outlined here:<br /><br />
      <div class=hang><a href="life/"><b>His Life</b></a> provides information on Lovecraft&rsquo;s
         life, family, correspondents, interests, and a photo gallery;</div>
      <div class=hang><a href="writings/"><b>His Writings</b></a> explores his wide variety of
         works, including his fiction and letters, and includes many electronic texts;</div>
      <div class=hang><a href="creation/"><b>His Creations</b></a> outlines his fictional elements
         including Lovecraftian locations in New England, a bestiary, and a list of grimoires;</div>
      <div class=hang><a href="study/"><b>His Study</b></a> has information on biographies,
         literary criticism, bibliographies, periodicals, and online articles;</div>
      <div class=hang><a href="popcult/"><b>Popular Culture</b></a> details the movies, games,
         music, and art based on Lovecraft&rsquo;s works, as well as the
         &ldquo;Cthulhu Mythos&rdquo;;</div>
      <div class=hang><a href="internet/"><b>Internet Resources</b></a> gives information on other
         Lovecraft-related sites, newsgroups, and FTP sites; and</div>
      <div class=hang><a href="about/"><b>About This Site</b></a> outlines the purpose and goals of
         this site.</div></td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
      <td valign=bottom width=88px><center><font size=-2>If you enjoy The H.P. Lovecraft Archive,
         consider donating:<br />
